  "text": "5 mg (3D) or 10 mg (2D) of protein from cell lysates or 4.5 ml media (3D) were prepared in a non-denaturing loading buffer and separated through an 8% SDS-polyacrylamide gel containing 0.08% gelatin, as described previously [CITATION_1] . Densitometric analysis was done using FluorChem software (AlphaInnotech). Total MMP-2, indicative of MMP-2 production, was analyzed as the sum of the latent (72 kDa) and activated (62 kDa) MMP-2 bands. Percent activated MMP-2, often an indirect indicator of the amount of MT1-MMP, is calculated as the ratio of activated MMP-2 to total MMP-2 [CITATION_2] .",
